                                "stop": 6.055,
                                "byte_start": 89576,
                                "byte_stop": 113818,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 00-189, Idaho versus United States will also be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.055,
                        "stop": 295.235,
                        "byte_start": 113818,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.055,
                                "stop": 11.823,
                                "byte_start": 113818,
                                "byte_stop": 136910,
                                "text": "This is my day."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.823,
                                "stop": 18.43,
                                "byte_start": 136910,
                                "byte_stop": 163346,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.43,
                                "stop": 30.549,
                                "byte_start": 163346,
                                "byte_stop": 211829,
                                "text": "It involves a dispute between the United States and the State of Idaho over ownership of submerged lands underlying portions of Lake Coeur d\u0027Alene and the St. Joe River."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.549,
                                "stop": 38.165,
                                "byte_start": 211829,
                                "byte_stop": 242340,
                                "text": "The disputed lands are within a vast area that was once inhabited by the Coeur d\u2019Alene Tribe of Indians."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.165,
                                "stop": 49.569,
                                "byte_start": 242340,
                                "byte_stop": 287898,
                                "text": "In 1873, in the phase of an influx of immigration into that tribal territory, President Grant set aside an exclusive tribal reservation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.569,
                                "stop": 61.477,
                                "byte_start": 287898,
                                "byte_stop": 335545,
                                "text": "During the 1880s, the Tribe and the United States negotiated over the size of that reservation and over the Tribe\u2019s continuing claim to other aboriginal lands."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.477,
                                "stop": 71.669,
                                "byte_start": 335545,
                                "byte_stop": 376296,
                                "text": "Although they reached several agreements, before the agreements were ratified by Congress, the State of Idaho was admitted into the Union in 1890."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.669,
                                "stop": 89.886,
                                "byte_start": 376296,
                                "byte_stop": 449125,
                                "text": "It was not until eight months later that Congress approved the agreements by which the Tribe ceded aboriginal lands and part of the 1873 reservation in return for compensation and for congressional confirmation of the reservation that remained."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.886,
                                "stop": 100.848,
                                "byte_start": 449125,
                                "byte_stop": 493011,
                                "text": "In 1994, the United States sued Idaho to determine ownership of the portion of the lakebed and the riverbed within the Tribe\u2019s current reservation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.848,
                                "stop": 106.913,
                                "byte_start": 493011,
                                "byte_stop": 517253,
                                "text": "The District Court quieted title in favor of the United States as trustee for the Tribe."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.913,
                                "stop": 110.16,
                                "byte_start": 517253,
                                "byte_stop": 530314,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.16,
                                "stop": 118.313,
                                "byte_start": 530314,
                                "byte_stop": 562915,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari and in an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we affirm the judgment of the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.313,
                                "stop": 128.479,
                                "byte_start": 562915,
                                "byte_stop": 603561,
                                "text": "Due to the public importance of the navigable waterways, ownership of the land under such waters is closely identified with the sovereign power of government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.479,
                                "stop": 152.719,
                                "byte_start": 603561,
                                "byte_stop": 700528,
                                "text": "A court deciding a question of title to the bed of navigable water must therefore begin with a strong presumption in favor of State\u2019s title and with that presumption, we have looked to Congress\u2019 declarations and intent in order to resolve conflicts over submerged lands that it claimed to have been conveyed or reserved by the United States before statehood."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.719,
                                "stop": 162.184,
                                "byte_start": 700528,
                                "byte_stop": 738353,
                                "text": "Via submerged lands beneath navigable waters are located in the tract that National Government has reserved for a particular national purpose."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.184,
                                "stop": 173.384,
                                "byte_start": 738353,
                                "byte_stop": 783179,
                                "text": "We asked whether Congress intended to include the submerged lands within the federal reservation, and if so, whether Congress intended to defeat the future State\u2019s title."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.384,
                                "stop": 193.258,
                                "byte_start": 783179,
                                "byte_stop": 862696,
                                "text": "This two step test of congressional intent can be satisfied in the context of land reserved by the Executive Branch, if the Executive reservation clearly included submerged lands and Congress recognized the reservation in a way that demonstrates an intent to defeat state title."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.258,
                                "stop": 207.395,
                                "byte_start": 862696,
                                "byte_stop": 919225,
                                "text": "Here, Idaho has conceded that the Executive Branch intended the 1873 Executive water reservation to include submerged lands and that by 1888 Congress was on notice of that fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.395,
                                "stop": 217.013,
                                "byte_start": 919225,
                                "byte_stop": 957677,
                                "text": "Both of those concessions are sound in light of the District Court findings that we found in detail in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.013,
                                "stop": 230.061,
                                "byte_start": 957677,
                                "byte_stop": 1009922,
                                "text": "The manner in which Congress proceeded to deal with the Tribe made it plain that Congress\u2019 object was to obtain tribal interests and modify the extent of the reservation only by tribal consent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.061,
                                "stop": 238.572,
                                "byte_start": 1009922,
                                "byte_stop": 1043881,
                                "text": "Its object was therefore necessarily to deny Idaho title to any unrelinquished submerged lands within the reservation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 238.572,
                                "stop": 254.097,
                                "byte_start": 1043881,
                                "byte_stop": 1106053,
                                "text": "Congress, for example, undertook in an 1889 Act to authorize negotiations with the Tribe for the consensual compensated session of such portions of the reservation as the Tribe would consent to sell."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.097,
                                "stop": 263.458,
                                "byte_start": 1106053,
                                "byte_stop": 1143460,
                                "text": "This and other evidence shows that Congress\u2019 intent was clearly that anything not ceded by the Tribe would remain for the Tribe\u2019s benefit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 263.458,
                                "stop": 278.09,
                                "byte_start": 1143460,
                                "byte_stop": 1201974,
                                "text": "An object that is flatly at odds with Idaho\u2019s view that Congress meant to transfer submerged lands to the State in what would have amounted to an active bad faith accomplished by the unspoken operation of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 278.09,
                                "stop": 288.244,
                                "byte_start": 1201974,
                                "byte_stop": 1242621,
                                "text": "Idaho\u2019s position is also at odds with later manifestations of congressional understanding that statehood had not affected title to the submerged lands."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.244,
                                "stop": 295.235,
                                "byte_start": 1242621,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Scalia, Kennedy and Thomas join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
